    <string name="manual">\n
        Items for Attack and Defense are organized in separate lists. Additionally there is a third tab for
        dice rolls concerning your character.\n
        \n
        An Item has these properties:\n
        - Active (in the Dicepool)\n
        - Name\n
        - Number for each die\n
        \n
        On clicking the \'Roll\' button all dice of all active Items of the respective list are gathered and rolled. The result is
        then displayed beside the \'Roll\' button. \'X\' means Miss.\n
        \n
        On long-clicking an Item a context-menu is displayed. Here you can delete or edit the Item. In the Edit-Dialog
        the name of the Item and the number of each die-type can be set. The items in the \'Hero\' tab are read-only.\n
        \n
        On clicking the \'Probability\' button a table is displayed. Here the MINIMAL probabilities are displayed for all
        possible combinations of range and damage for the current dicepool.
        For example, if for range = 4 and damage = 2 the value is 23.34 percent, then it means, that with 23.34 percent
        probability the roll-result shows a combination with range >= 4 and damage >= 2.\n
        \n
        For the current roll result a click on the \'Info\' button opens a detail view for the roll result.
        Here single dice can be rolled separately by clicking on them.
    </string>
